communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Kobe Bean Bryant Death
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

I would like to request any records referencing or referring to the American athlete Kobe Bean Bryant. If any possibly relevant records have been destroyed and/or moved to NARA, I demand copies of the destruction or transfer papers and any other paperwork pertaining to, referencing, or detailing said transfer or destruction, including but not limited to assurance that the Bureau has no additional copies of said records.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Shaira roscom

title: FCC Complaints about Miley Cyrus VMA Awards Performance

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: FCC Complaints about Miley Cyrus VMA Awards Performance
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any complaints received by the FCC regarding the August 25, 2013 performance by Miley Cyrus at the 2013 Video Music Awards aired on MTV.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Shaira roscom
